          {
            "title": "Intro",
            "id": 78645,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>So far we've learned how to create a <code>while</code> loop, now let's focus on how to stop them from looping infinitely.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;and again&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Looks like your code runs forever. It may be that an infinite loop exists in your code.\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Creating the variable",
            "id": 78648,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To stop a loop, we start by creating a variable outside of the loop.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"keep_going = \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;and again&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"10\" /><option startIndex=\"11\" endIndex=\"12\" /><option startIndex=\"13\" endIndex=\"17\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"print\" /></content></option><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\":\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Looks like your code runs forever. It may be that an infinite loop exists in your code.\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>keep_going</code>, followed by <code>=</code>, and finally <code>True</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Variable in the condition",
            "id": 78647,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We use the variable in the condition to decide whether or not the loop should run its code block. For example, <code>keep_going == True</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"keep_going = \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" keep_going == \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;and again&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"25\" endIndex=\"35\" /><option startIndex=\"36\" endIndex=\"38\" /><option startIndex=\"39\" endIndex=\"43\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Looks like your code runs forever. It may be that an infinite loop exists in your code.\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>keep_going</code>, followed by <code>==</code>, and finally <code>True</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Updating the variable",
            "id": 78670,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Inside the code block, we stop the loop by setting <code>keep_going</code> to <code>False</code> so that the condition returns <code>False</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"keep_going = \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" keep_going == \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;and again&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  keep_going = \" /><text value=\"False\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"81\" endIndex=\"86\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"and again\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>False</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Stopping the loop",
            "id": 78644,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>The loop runs its entire code block because <code>keep_going</code> is <code>True</code> at first, but doesn't run again if we set <code>keep_going</code> to <code>False</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"keep_going = \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" keep_going == \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;and again&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  keep_going = \" /><text value=\"False\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;one more time&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"and again\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"one more time\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Creating the variable",
            "id": 78643,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>How do we know this loop runs and never stops repeating its code block?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"load_data = \" /><text value=\"False\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"while\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Loading data..&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"Loading data..\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Loading data..\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Loading data..\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Looks like your code runs forever. It may be that an infinite loop exists in your code.\" /></content></output></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">There's no variable in the condition</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">This loop won't run since the condition is <code>False</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">There's no variable in the condition.</p></body></html>"
          },
